  "title": "Clinic Nurse (Plastic Surgery/ Staff & Enrolled Nurse) #81797",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Healthcare/ Medical (Plastic Surgery Clinic)</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Clinic Nurse</strong></li><li>Working Location: Novena (Walk distance from MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 Days; Mon-Fri (9am - 6pm) Sat (9am – 1pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + OT + AWS + Bonus + Medical & Dental Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide nursing care and support for patients undergoing consultations, minor procedures, and post-operative follow-ups.</li><li>Assist the doctor during in-clinic procedures.</li><li>Perform clinical duties such as vital signs monitoring, patient preparation, and post-procedure observation.</li><li>Educate patients on pre- and post-procedure instructions, medication compliance, wound care, and recovery expectations.</li><li>Maintain accurate clinical documentation and patient records in accordance with clinic standards.</li><li>Support infection control measures, sterilisation, and proper handling of instruments/ consumables.</li><li>Manage clinic inventory (medical supplies, medications if applicable), stock ordering, and expiry checks.</li><li>Coordinate appointments, follow-ups, and patient enquiries as required, working closely with the clinic team.</li><li>Ensure compliance with relevant clinic policies and regulatory requirements.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Nitec or Diploma in Nursing, ideally SNB-registered.</li><li>At least 1 year of working experience as an Enrolled Nurse/ Staff Nurse.</li><li>Comfortable with a patient-facing role and able to communicate clearly and professionally.</li><li>Strong attention to detail, good hygiene/ infection control practice, and ability to work independently.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81797 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
